    Product Description

    Carry and Store your Nintendo Switch, Enjoy the Game Anytime Anywhere You Want

    UGREEN accessory bag case is specially designed for Nintendo Switch and other accessories. It is convenient to carry when you go out

    for visiting or vocation and well stored when it is not in use. Everything will be well organized and protected.

    Just One Case is Enough, Keep your Nintendo Switch and Accessories Tidy

    The bottom layer with inserted foam is for your Joy-Con Grip with Controller and power adapter. The front side of the middle board with elastic strip can hold the console tightly, the rear side of the board is 10 cards cartridges,

    • At top, there is a zippered mesh pocket, which offers enough room for extra Joy-Cons, Joy-Con straps, earbuds, charging cables, flash drive etc.
    • Material: EVA+ Oxford Cloth
    • Dimension: 260*135*88mm
    • Extra Carabiner for hung at your backpack

    Excellent Protection from All Side

    Inside Protection:

    • The inner soft and shock-resistant foam at bottom can greatly protect devices from scratch; the Accurate Groove inside the carrying case perfectly fits the controller and power adapter, keeping firmly, no waggle and squeezing. The two Elastic Strips and thick Velvet board greatly protect the console from scratch and bumping. The mesh pocket at the top layer can protect the accessories from scratch, the zipper design prevent the small little items from falling out.

    • The shell of the bag made of hard EVA and Oxford material, it is very tough and durable, can prevent your device from bumping and great pressure during transportation.
    • Double zipper design is quite smooth to pull, durable and rust protection.
    • The material used is odorless. Quite safe to use.

        Wazat
        3.0 out of 5 stars A bit tight, puts pressure on the joysticks
        Reviewed in the United States on July 9, 2019
        Verified Purchase
        I'm updating this review after seeing other options, then getting a different case and liking it a lot more. My earlier review was naive.

        My new case takes special care to ensure no pressure is on the joysticks, and I really like that protection. It also stores all accessories (including the dock) but it's much larger, so I'm not holding that against this one. This product's main problem is your joysticks are not well-protected, and that's a potentially expensive mistake. I want my joysticks to last a long time and stay responsive, and sitting with pressure on them is not a good way to achieve that. After seeing what my friends use and after getting a different case for myself, I'm no longer impressed at all with this one. I'll be giving this one away.

        My old review is below, with some updates to be more accurate to my experience after using the case more:

        I greatly appreciate having a hard container standing between the fumbling, flailing, stomping world and my expensive Switch. Stupid people will throw luggage around, stomp hard with their feet, etc; I like knowing my switch will survive their efforts.

        My main concern is the pressure put on the controller sticks unless I remove the two joycons and store them separately in the compartment below, *sideways* so no pressure is on those joysticks (nevermind the pictures advertising this case; that's false advertising, you'd never want to store your switch like that).

        There's room below to store the AC plug and cords, and the controller that attaches to the joycons, but it gets tight down there. Again, hard to protect the joysticks. It does not store anything else, like the dock or other accessories. It includes slots for games, though it would be nice if the strap were higher so I could see the game labels without pulling each game out one at a time.

        rvcjew
        5.0 out of 5 stars Not perfect in stock form but with some tweaking is perfect if you own certain accessories.
        Reviewed in the United States on May 15, 2018
        Verified Purchase
        UGREEN Carring Case for Nintendo Switch, W/Carved Protective Foam Lining, Shockproof Travel Case Bag for Nintendo Switch Console, AC Wall Charger, Grip and Joy-con, 10 Game Cards, Strap and CablesFancyWolf Nintendo Switch Replacement Dock Portable DIY Dock Mount Case BlackJoy-Con Gel Guards with Thumb Grips Caps for Nintendo Switch (Black)
        Orzly Glass Screen Protectors compatible with Nintendo Switch - Premium Tempered Glass Screen Protector TWIN PACK [2x Screen Guards - 0.24mm] for 6.2 Inch Tablet Screen on Nintendo Switch Console

        I needed a case to make the switch very portable in every aspect and this one I was able to modify to exactly that (it's not that pretty but is function over form). I used the linked accessories and they make the switch thicker then a stock one and I also wanted to carry the dock in a smaller replacement case then what is offered for the stock dock as those cases are either a: to tall, b: has molding for a completely flat switch, or c: not the right dimensions for what I needed. It now fits the dock, games, ac adapter, hdmi cable, switch with thicker joycons attached, or the switch with thick joycons attached plus the battery I linked on the switch all with out removing the joycons from it to travel with it.

        What I did:
        I cut out the In my opinion useless (but it does add top padding and rigidity to the case) top zipper pouch then added my own foam with velcro (can be removed if the battery is on the switch) so that there is still space for the joycons to sit in the shell.

        I cut the elastic strips off the soft side of the screen cover and cut the shapes you see so the joycons do not touch it and the sticks are free and not squished.

        I cut the stock foam to better fit all my stuff and made a plug with the excess to make sure the case side is rigid when closed (otherwise it can be squeezed very easily).

        It can fit a pro controller and ac adapter if you want to do that on the bottom instead of the dock.

        If I would do it over I would cut the foam cleaner (went through a lot of test shapes) and use black foam for up top to clean it up.

        Malcolm

        TJP
        5.0 out of 5 stars Smells horrible, but a great case once you air it out
        Reviewed in the United States on July 11, 2019
        Verified Purchase
        I needed a case that could carry my Switch, joycons with grip, stand, power brick and cable, a few games, and headphones. Most that meet those requirements also have room for the dock, which I do not ever take with me. This one works perfectly for what I wanted without any extra bulkiness. Only caveats worth mentioning is that the OEM charger doesn't really fit in the spot allocated for it (it looks more like the cutout is for a euro or asian plug rather than US)... and the smell. I don't take the Nintendo charger with me anyway since that's always hooked up to the dock; I have a Inateck one that fits in there fine since the USB-C cable is detachable, and there's just enough extra room for the official charging stand in that spot as well.

        As for the smell, it's godawful at first. I tried Febreze, I tried an aquarium charcoal filter, I tried leaving it outside... I think the charcoal worked best, but it still took a week or so to get it from "overpowering stench" down to merely "mildly offensive". Not really unexpected though, anything with that kind of foam is going to smell awful unless it's aired out at the factory first.
